               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18440205-name-1139" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18440205-name-1139" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18440205-name-1139" type="surname" value="HOWARD"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18440205-name-1139" type="given" value="MARY"></interp>MARY HOWARD</persName>
                  </hi>. I am servant to Mr. William Ballinger. On the 4th of Feb., at night, I was in the back parlour— I saw brown come into the shop,take a jar of tobacco, and go out to the step of the door, and hand it to Barry— I am sure he is the person— I gave information and went and caught Brown, but I did not get the jar— Barry handed it away to two accomplices.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Cross examined by</hi> 
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">Mr Horry</hi> 
                  <hi rend="italic">Q.</hi> How far did Barry go with it? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> A little way, and then handed it to two other boys — Brown would have run away, but i caught hold of him, and my mistress came out— Barry crossed the road, then came back and stood there, and when the policeman came up I gave him into custody.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Brown</hi> I went past the prosecutor's shop, and a man said, "What have you got?" I said, "Nothing;" the woman then came out, and said "This is one;" she told the man to hold me; she swore that all she knew me by was my blue jacket and white trowsers; I said I had not white trowsers, but fustian; she said, "Whether or not, it is you;" I am quite a stranger to this boy.</p>
               <p>
                  <persName id="t18440205-name-1140" type="witnessName">
